{
  "_comment": "Per-pitfall classification of operational verifiability. Two fields per entry: `falsifiable` (can a programmatic test EVER settle whether the Signal fired?) and `cost` (how much fixture code is needed to do so). Used by scripts/verify_signal_clauses.py to compute an HONEST scoreboard: tier2_passed / n_realistically_verifiable instead of tier2_passed / 96.",
  "_methodology": "Walked each deal.II catalog pitfall's Signal: clause. Classified by inspection. Falsifiable=false only when the Signal cannot in principle be settled by a test (subjective, process advice, performance without an SLA). Cost categories: 'cheap' (<=80 lines C++/Py, no PDE solve required), 'medium' (full PDE solve + analytic reference required), 'expensive' (needs profiler / MPI / long-time integration / specific solver build).",
  "_schema": {
    "<backend>::<physics>::<pitfall_index>": {
      "falsifiable": true,
      "cost": "cheap | medium | expensive",
      "method": "exception_class | numerical_comparison | structural_query | runtime_observation | performance_profile | mpi_invariant",
      "notes": "short rationale"
    }
  },
